HEADWORD: Dryfland
<hw>Dryf"land</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Drove</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>An ancient yearly payment made by some tenants to the king, or to
their landlords, for the privilege of driving their cattle through a
manor to fairs or markets.</def> <rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

